Prof Dave's English Learning Blog




Inspiring university students in Taiwan to learn English more effectively 

































































































高級英文寫作
















My Office: Research Building 405

My Email: davegerich2@gmail.com (Don't forget the 2. It's for students only.)



Updated:

June 12, 2017


Homework:

Practice writing the Argumentative Essay based on the pros and cons list that you completed last week for homework. 

Write a detailed outline for your essay, choosing either block or point-by-point style. My intention of teaching you the "basic" style was to show you a simpler way of writing the argumentative essay, but the block and point-by-point are more persuasive, so on the final exam, you will need to write either block or point-by-point style. 

Then write the essay according to the models that we studied in class last week. You can type or write this assignment by hand. It will count as a homework assignment but not a major assignment. The major assignment is to write a new argumentative essay in class as your final exam. I will give you the topic and research info that you need for your essay in class on Friday.

Here are some helpful references:

Argumentative Essay Block Organization Example

Argumentative Essay Overview on PPT
Note: The example of a point-by-point style outline is in the textbook (page 157).






















